        "text": "Distretto Italia is planning a national action plan to carry out orientation activities for girls and boys of school age. Through a practical and interactive approach, young people will be able to experience different trades and identify the professional path that best matches their interests and abilities.\n\nThis need starts by listening to over 700 students and over 200 parents and lecturers. The results showed that the orientation paths must include phygital experiences, a continuous exchange with professionals, guide to the discovery of trades and accompany young people to discover themselves.\n\nGuidance activities respond to the need to prepare young people adequately for the challenges of the labour market and is intended as a catalyst for wider social transformation, promoting a development model based on direct knowledge and practical experience."
